78.0	Charles_Lyell	Charles Lyell	Sir Charles Lyell, 1st Baronet, Kt FRS (14 November 1797 – 22 February 1875) was a British lawyer and the foremost geologist of his day. He is best known as the author of Principles of Geology, which popularised James Hutton's concepts of uniformitarianism – the idea that the earth was shaped by slow-moving forces still in operation today. Lyell was a close and influential friend of Charles Darwin.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/50/Charles_Lyell00.jpg/220px-Charles_Lyell00.jpg
